               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dāwit “Psalter” (fols. 1r-161vb)
 I-1) Mazmura Dāwit “Psalms of
                     David” (fols. 1r-124v) 
 I-2) Maḥālǝya nabiyāt “The Canticles of the
                     Prophets” (fols. 125r-138r) 
 I-3) Maḥālǝya maḥālǝy “Song of Songs” (fols.
                     138r-145r) 
 I-4) Wǝddāse Māryām “Praise of Mary” (fols. 145ra-156vb) 
                     I-5) ʾAnqaṣa bǝrhān “The Gate of Light” (fols. 156vb-161vb)
 II)
                     Historiographic note on the Tablets of Law and on ʾAksum (fol. 164r)
 III)
                     Ṣalota nadarā, ʾAsmat-prayer against a disease called nädära and against an
                     evil eye (fols. 165r-168v)
 
 Additiones 1-2.</summary>

               </msContents>
